headline: CNC Q1 Earnings Call: Centene Raises Revenue Guidance Amid Policy Headwinds and Margin Stability
summary: Health coverage company Centene (NYSE:CNC) reported Q1 CY2025 results exceeding the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 15.4% year on year to $46.62 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $180 billion at the midpoint came in 4.2% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.90 per share was 15.3% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
